sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT tos.treatment_id) AS total_treatments_with_positive_outcomes
FROM treatment_outcomes tos
WHERE tos.outcome_value = 'Successful';

external_knowledge:
- 'False positive rate' is the rate at which a treatment incorrectly identifies a condition when it is not present;
- 'Treatment equality score' measures how equally a treatment affects different demographic groups;
- 'Demographic attribute values' include categories such as race (e.g., African-American) and gender (e.g., Female).

sql:
